	<Title>
		Love to bike? Remember a helmet
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;A helmet is essential fitness gear for bikers. After all, without a helmet, you risk a head injury every time you head out on your bike. When you&apos;re choosing a bike helmet, remember the ground rules: 1. Make sure the helmet is safe. Look for a seal of approval from the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC). 2. Make sure the helmet fits snugly. You shouldn&apos;t be able to move the helmet more than 1 inch (2.5 centimeters) in any direction, front to back or side to side. 3. Think about visibility. Choose a white or brightly colored helmet that will be easy for motorists to see.&lt;/p&gt;
	</Body>
